# FSx, Storage Gateway & the decision

## FSx — specialised file systems

- **Windows File Server** — SMB, NTFS, **AD** — any Windows/SMB question
- **Lustre** — **HPC / ML**, hundreds of GB/s, links to an **S3 bucket**
- **NetApp ONTAP** (NFS+SMB+iSCSI) · **OpenZFS** — lift-and-shift

## Storage Gateway — on-prem bridge

- **S3 File Gateway** — on-prem files → S3
- **Volume Gateway** (iSCSI) — block, S3/EBS-backed
- **Tape Gateway** — replace physical tape (→ S3/Glacier)

## The file decision

Linux NFS → **EFS** · Windows/AD → **FSx Windows** · HPC/ML → **FSx Lustre** · on-prem→S3 → **File Gateway**.
**Default: EFS for Linux, FSx for Windows.**
